# Isometric rendering and maps

- **Z-order / depth:** Always consider draw order; sort entities by a `Depth` value derived from screen-space position (e.g. screen Y) before issuing draws.
- **Batching:** Group draw calls by texture/material to minimize state changes.
- **Tilemaps:** Prefer flattened 1D arrays for 2D/3D grid data for cache locality.
- **Coordinates:** Follow the coordinate and depth conventions documented in **`.cursor/docs/architecture.md`** (*Isometric Rendering Rules*). Update that section when conventions change.
